		<div>You want zero flames it means that we need an area that people can read without being able to post. Then they can submit questions to be asked via PM or another thread. If they can maintain a level or responsibility &amp; control then they may be able to EARN the right to post directly to the boards.<br />
<br />
The caveat to this is that the Dev needs to actually provide responses to EVERY question that is posted. Even if the answer is &quot;I can't answer that due to legal obligations&quot; or some such legalese. We require some responses from someone. <br />
<br />
In many of the classes I have attended for various training on products &amp; such the teachers have adopted a &quot;Parking Lot&quot;. This is for questions that they can't answer off the top of their heads. We could use something similar if we could just get a Dev to buy in. He can't answer since he does not work on that but he can go to the person who does to get some sort of clarification.<br />
<br />
It can work but we need to get some buy in &amp; commitment from some SOE rep. Till then it is just smoke &amp; mirrors.</div>
