	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Gem, I don't think another sit down would help out, to be honest. They have done this before and it did not lead to the major issues being addressed. The problem is that most all the classes on EQ1 have complaints, many valid, and right now it is a huge quagmire and entanglement that may be almost impossible to get out of unless a major revamp of the game takes place.<br />
<br />
Whizbang is now Ringo, a Hunter on WoW of good repute who leads a good guild on the Silver Hand server. I play a Warlock on the Argent Dawn server and am at level 45 now..so for myself and others there is the perspective of how things are done there as compared to EQ1. Mr. Smedley has stated that many at SOE has played WoW, and I think your beginning to see some of the dynamics of that game being introduced into EQ1..especially with the last expansion. An example of this is the Corpse summoner. <br />
<br />
The big difference I see between the two is that on WoW the interdependancy of the classes is not paramount, and one can go out and do things solo for a bit such as doing quests and actually progress in the game..and yet group and raid for instanced zones and other &quot;elite&quot; quests which require team work. On EQ1 I still have to have two things available to me in order to do anything..KEI from an enchanter and access to a cleric who can Rez me if I die out there somewhere.<br />
<br />
SOE needs to decide what to do with EQ1 and where it stands in the comparison with other games out there..a new vision. Is it a hard core raiding game that requires many hours of on line participation? Where does a casual player fit in? What incentive is there for someone new to load EQ1 on their computer and log on for the first time? What should the balance be between solo questing and group particpation in order to advance?..some basic stuff and is not related to class balance so much as the overall health of the game itself.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				Nukes R Us
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		
		
		
	
	</td>
